You can package this class as part of a custom Spring Boot starter library, which can be included as a dependency in other applications. And, when the application starts it will automatically import the configuration class and set the custom ErrorMessageProcessor globally for all binders.

It is important to note that this approach will work only if the application is running in a single context mode, if it's running in a multi context mode, you will have to configure the error message processor on each context individually.

