One way to fix this error is to make sure that the data you are trying to send is in one of these formats. For example, if you are trying to send a JavaScript object as part of the request, you will need to convert it to a string first using `JSON.stringify()`.

Here is an example of how to fix this error using `JSON.stringify()`:


```
const data = {
 username: 'John Doe',
 password: 'my-secret-password'
};

// Convert the data to a string
const dataString = JSON.stringify(data);

// Send the request with the stringified data
axios.post('https://example.com/login', dataString)
 .then(response => {
 // Handle the response
 })
 .catch(error => {
 // Handle the error
 });
```
If you are not trying to send any data with the request, you can simply pass `null` as the second argument to `axios.post()`, like this:


```
axios.post('https://example.com/login', null)
 .then(response => {
 // Handle the response
 })
 .catch(error => {
 // Handle the error
 });
```
