In this `Controller` class, the `__construct` method is used to inject the model object that will be used by the controller. This allows the controller to access the data and application logic provided by the model. The `processRequest` method is used to handle requests from the user and to dispatch them to the appropriate action method in the controller. If the specified action method does not exist, the `index` method is used as the default action. This allows the controller to be easily extended by adding new action methods as needed, without having to modify the core `Controller` class. Overall, this is a simple and flexible approach to implementing a controller in PHP using OOP principles.

