To enable query logging in TypeORM, you can use the `logging` option in the `createConnection` method. The `logging` option can be set to one of the following values:

* `false` (or `false`): disable query logging
* `true` (or `"all"`): log all queries
* `"query"`: log only queries, without parameters
* `"schema"`: log schema build/sync operations
* `"error"`: log only errors
* A custom function for logging: this function will be called for every executed query, and it will receive the executed query and query parameters as arguments.

Here is an example of how you can enable query logging in TypeORM:


```
import { createConnection } from "typeorm";

createConnection({
 // other options
 logging: true, // or "all"
});
```
This will log all queries to the console. You can also use a custom function for logging:


```
import { createConnection } from "typeorm";

const myLoggingFn = (query: string, parameters: any[]) => {
 // do something with the executed query and parameters
};

createConnection({
 // other options
 logging: myLoggingFn,
});
```
